From 065bc234bd8ae110d66ef1cc0e2dd5a05320ded0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthias Petermann <mp@petermann-it.de>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 06:59:43 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] cellmgr/cellctl: add declarative run-as for supervised
 services

Supervised workloads previously defaulted to root, which is unsafe and can
cause ownership inconsistencies when isolated services write to shared storage.
This change introduces an explicit runtime identity contract for supervised
commands and applies it end-to-end.

- add cellmgr --run-as / CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_AS
  (host:user[:group] or uid:uid[:gid])
- resolve run-as identities to numeric credentials during apply
- render runtime-only CELL_SUPERVISE_RUN_UID/GID/GROUPS into cell.conf
- treat both run-as intent and resolved credentials as service drift
- extend cellctl supervise with -U/-G/-g and drop credentials in strict order
  after chroot and cell enter: setgroups -> setgid -> setuid
- fail closed when run-as is configured but runtime credentials are missing
- update docs/manpages and expose run-as in cell output fields

This makes supervised startup deterministic, enforces least privilege by
default, and keeps file ownership behavior consistent across host/cell
boundaries without coupling identity handling to mount-specific logic.
