 limit behavior.
-.It Cm supervise Op Fl f Ar facility Op Fl o Ar stdout-level Op Fl e Ar stderr-level Op Fl t Ar tag Ar cell-id | name Ar command Op Ar args ...
+.It Cm supervise Op Fl f Ar facility Op Fl o Ar stdout-level Op Fl e Ar stderr-level Op Fl t Ar tag Op Fl U Ar uid Op Fl G Ar gid Op Fl g Ar gid[,gid...] Ar cell-id | name Ar command Op Ar args ...
 Start a command in an existing cell selected by
 .Ar cell-id
 or
@@ -182,8 +185,39 @@ Set the syslog tag used for forwarded celled-command output.
 If omitted,
 .Dq cellctl
 is used.
+.It Fl U Ar uid
+Drop supervised child credentials to this numeric user id after
+.Xr chroot 2
+and
+the cell membership switch has completed.
+.It Fl G Ar gid
+Drop supervised child credentials to this numeric primary group id.
+When
+.Fl U
+is used,
+.Fl G
+is required, and vice versa.
+.It Fl g Ar gid[,gid...]
+Set supplementary groups for supervised children.
+This option requires
+.Fl U
+and
+.Fl G .
+When omitted while
+.Fl U
+and
+.Fl G
+are provided, supplementary groups are cleared.
 .El
 .Pp
+When credential drop options are configured, the supervisor applies them in
+the order
+.Xr setgroups 2 ,
+.Xr setgid 2 ,
+then
+.Xr setuid 2
+after entering the cell root and kernel cell membership.
+.Pp
 The background supervisor process is shown in process listings as
 .Dq cellctl supervise cell=<name> cid=<id>
 to distinguish it from one-shot supervise invocations.
